Apprs: CO: SRN, Rpr: Kasten, Clerk: Evenson. ADA: Michael Edward Nieskes DF ATTY: Eric C. Thole DF: Tracy Ann Breault appeared. Case called at 2:09. State has filed an amended information amending to 3 misdemeanor counts covering 2 calendar years. Atty. Thole responds. Court reads charge and maximum penalty to 3 counts of misdemeanor theft. DE pleads G to Ct 1, 2 and 3 in 15CF235. DE sworn. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of Ct 1, 2 and 3 in 15CF235. Sentencing arguments. Victims make a statement. DE makes statement. Crt orders: Sentence W/H on all 3 counts
Ct. 1
2 years probation with conditions:
    Probation to run concurrent with MN probation. 
- 12 days St. Croix County Jail no good time.
   Huber granted for employment.
   DE to confirm dates with St. Croix County or with Washington County within the first 60 days of probation.
- Costs of $243.00 on all 3 Counts.
- Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge of $200 on all 3 Counts.
- DE to have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, Somerset Girls Softball organization including meetings and games or board memebers .  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, through the mail, and/or through a third person.
- Apology letter to Somerset Community and a letter to the Somerset Board Members to be completed within 30 days. 
  Court has no objection to the Somerset community letter being published if ok with the board members. 
- DE is to maintain her current mental health treatment.
- DE to participate in restorative justice.
- 80 hours community service at the discretion of the agent. 

Ct. 2
- 2 years probation concurrent to Ct. 1

Ct. 3
- 2 years probation concurrent to Ct. 1
   Probation is concurrent without prejudice to consecutive sentencing in the event of Probation revocation.



Court has no objection to DE serving the 12 days in Washington County as in custody only.
Plea hearing on April 18, 2016 at 02:00 pm.

Initial appearance on July 23, 2015 at 01:00 pm.

It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, Somerset Girls Softball organization of principals (participation at the games is authorized).  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, through the mail, and/or through a third person.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.

Further, it is ORDERED that if the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bailjumping contrary to Sec. 946.49(1)(a), Wis. Stats.
